1
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,040
Damn.

2
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,240
Damn.

3
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:03,480
Officer.

4
00:03:51,720 --> 00:03:52,480
Take them away.

5
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:53,160
Yes, sir.

6
00:03:58,079 --> 00:03:59,200
'The Song of the Volga Boatmen'

7
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:00,930
is a classic Russian folk song.

8
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:03,200
Its melody is heavy and deep,

9
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:06,970
expressing the hardship and resilience of the lower class.

10
00:04:13,040 --> 00:04:13,560
Get off.

11
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:14,520
Hurry up.

12
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:17,720
Stop.

13
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:18,860
Don't move.

14
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,320
Surround this place.

15
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:21,050
Surround it.

16
00:04:31,400 --> 00:04:32,080
Search.

17
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:33,480
Routine inspection.

18
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:36,980
What are you doing?

19
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:38,600
Sit down.

20
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,240
Sit down.

21
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:41,600
Did you hear me?

22
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:44,480
This is a cultural institution founded

23
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:45,600
by Mr. Schiller, a German.

24
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:47,360
According to the agreement, you must have the German Embassy

25
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:48,880
or Mr. Schiller's written authorization

26
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:49,600
to search.

27
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:50,880
Cut the crap.

28
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:55,520
Don't let me find anything,

29
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:57,810
or none of you will get away.

30
00:04:58,680 --> 00:05:00,440
Report. No radio station found here.

31
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:01,640
Report. Nothing on my side.

32
00:05:01,640 --> 00:05:03,640
Report. Nothing in the yard either.

33
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:06,280
Search the second floor.

34
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:07,160
You can't go to the second floor.

35
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:08,690
It's the teachers' office.

36
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,480
I'll shoot you dead.

37
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:13,960
Believe it or not?

38
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:15,880
Wait.

39
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:23,380
If you want to search, do it properly.

40
00:05:23,920 --> 00:05:24,920
Officer,

41
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:27,210
is there a need for weapons?

42
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,480
Xiaoxiong, get up.

43
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:35,120
Are you alright?

44
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,080
Who are you?

45
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:44,560
Miss Qin.

46
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:46,320
Mr. Matsuda,

47
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:47,840
is it really you?

48
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:49,400
Yes.

49
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:52,960
I haven't seen you for years.

50
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:55,760
I almost couldn't recognize you, Miss Qin.

51
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:57,640
You too, Mr. Matsuda.

52
00:05:57,760 --> 00:05:59,760
You seem like a different person.

53
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,580
Is your father doing well?

54
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:02,960
Thanks to you,

55
00:06:03,320 --> 00:06:05,720
he is still fiddling with his antiques.

56
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:09,200
Why did you stop doing antique business, Mr. Matsuda?

57
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:12,560
I've washed my hands of it.

58
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:14,880
Why are you here?

59
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:18,280
This is a harmonica club I opened with a German friend.

60
00:06:18,280 --> 00:06:19,000
Chief.

61
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:21,780
Miss Qin is so familiar with the Captain.

62
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:23,170
Should we still search?

63
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:25,890
Of course we should.

64
00:06:26,720 --> 00:06:28,160
You are on official duty.

65
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:31,240
You can't let personal matters interfere with public ones, right?

66
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,640
Miss Qin is right.

67
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:33,920
Search.

68
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,400
Don't be afraid, everyone.

69
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:42,200
It's just a routine inspection.

70
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:43,680
Xiaoxiong,

71
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,810
continue the class.

72
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,360
Mr. Matsuda, please.

73
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:52,010
Pardon the intrusion then.

74
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,320
Why are you so rude?

75
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:19,980
You can search,

76
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:22,170
but don't break Miss Qin's things.

77
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:26,560
Miss Qin.

78
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:27,960
Sorry.

79
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:31,000
I broke your gramophone.

80
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:32,970
I only know how to dismantle it.

81
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,210
I don't know how to pretend.

82
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:37,240
It's fine. I do.

83
00:07:38,159 --> 00:07:40,890
Qian Yugui, you're getting more and more unruly.

84
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:41,640
Yes.

85
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:44,250
It's okay, Mr. Matsuda.

86
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:45,159
Please sit.

87
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:49,040
Captain.

88
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:51,960
We've checked upstairs and found nothing.

89
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:56,560
Should we still search Miss Qin's bedroom?

90
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,720
It's fine. Go ahead.

91
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:05,200
It's not appropriate for me to do it with my clumsy hands.

92
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:07,000
Deputy Section Chief Chen.

93
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,920
You are careful. You go.

94
00:08:12,640 --> 00:08:13,520
Yes, Chief.

95
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:28,400
Try the tea.

96
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:01,960
Heming.

97
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:04,250
Pack up and go into the secret passage.

98
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:15,000
Be careful.

99
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:49,200
Traitor!

100
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:51,200
I don't know anything!

101
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:52,440
Bastard!

102
00:09:52,880 --> 00:09:53,600
Officer.

103
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:56,340
Actually, to deal with a girl,

104
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:59,440
there are many ways.

105
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:34,690
What's going on?

106
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:37,450
Captain, I'm sorry.

107
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,930
I didn't hold it steady.

108
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,320
Be careful.

109
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:43,960
If you don't find anything,

110
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:46,120
Miss Qin's private wardrobe,

111
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,180
stop searching it.

112
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,450
It's very impolite.

113
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:50,770
Why are you holding this small box?

114
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:52,560
Can it hold a radio?

115
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:53,280
Yes.

116
00:10:55,160 --> 00:10:56,000
However,

117
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:58,240
Miss Qin indeed studied abroad.

118
00:10:58,840 --> 00:10:59,900
She has good taste.

119
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:02,120
This French Hermès silk scarf

120
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:06,160
is very rare and beautiful.

121
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:08,040
Captain,

122
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:08,960
look.

123
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:11,440
Deputy Section Chief Chen is not only careful,

124
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:12,700
but also fashionable.

125
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:16,280
It's nothing.

126
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:19,250
If you like it, Deputy Section Chief Chen,

127
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:20,820
I'll give it to you.

128
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:22,570
I wouldn't dare.

129
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:26,120
Captain, we've searched the inner room.

130
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:26,880
No problem.

131
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:28,440
Miss Qin.

132
00:11:29,760 --> 00:11:31,320
Sorry to disturb you.

133
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:33,200
It's okay, Mr. Matsuda.

134
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,720
I hope you can visit the harmonica club often in the future.

135
00:11:35,720 --> 00:11:37,120
Captain, I'm sure

136
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:38,480
that the underground radio

137
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:39,840
is within 200 meters.

138
00:11:40,160 --> 00:11:42,080
If the operator hadn't stopped,

139
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:43,620
given another minute,

140
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:45,440
I could have found its exact location.

141
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,200
Suzuki.

142
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:49,560
Continue to detect radio waves in this area.

143
00:11:49,960 --> 00:11:52,040
I must find this radio.

144
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:55,360
Captain.

145
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:58,800
Miss Qin is a bit hard to read.

146
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:01,360
Qin Na is very smart.

147
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,050
She and her money-grubbing father

148
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:05,890
are not the same kind of people.

149
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,000
Captain.

150
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:11,400
These students in the harmonica club gathering together

151
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:12,560
is a hidden danger.

152
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:01,400
Who is it?

153
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:03,040
Speak.

154
00:14:27,160 --> 00:14:27,960
Zhu,

155
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,860
you work as a traitor for the Japanese

156
00:14:32,760 --> 00:14:34,620
and persecute your compatriots.

157
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:36,740
You deserve to die.

158
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:17,040
Brother, this is the fifth one, right?

159
00:15:17,040 --> 00:15:17,920
I know.
